com.reactivecascade.util

Class UIExecutorService

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.reactivecascade.util.Origin
      • com.reactivecascade.util.UIExecutorService
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IAsyncOrigin, Executor, ExecutorService

    public final class UIExecutorService
extends Origin
implements ExecutorService
    Treat the system UI thread as an ExecutorService

    This is done to allow UI codes to be part of UI IThreadType so that IAltFuture objects can be easily defined to run on the UI thread in Async.UI vs background worker threads.

    Since the system UI thread runs forever, not all ExecutorService items, for example related to lifecycle. make sense to implement.
